column13:
There are several datasets about UST on the Portal:
Regarding Tank Removal information, this data sets includes tank removal information in the column called Closure Type:
Underground Storage Tanks (USTs) - Facility and Tank Details (https://data.ct.gov/Environment-and-Natural-Resources/Underground-Storage-Tanks-USTs-Facility-and-Tank-D/utni-rddb); 
These 3 data sets may be of interest regarding Remediation:
Releases from Federally Regulated Underground Storage Tank Systems (https://data.ct.gov/Environment-and-Natural-Resources/Releases-from-Federally-Regulated-Underground-Stor/yc6z-jrb5);
List of Contaminated or Potentially Contaminated Sites - SASU Case Management System (https://data.ct.gov/Environment-and-Natural-Resources/List-of-Contaminated-or-Potentially-Contaminated-S/77ya-7twa);
List of Contaminated or Potentially Contaminated Sites - Remediation Division (https://data.ct.gov/Environment-and-Natural-Resources/List-of-Contaminated-or-Potentially-Contaminated-S/u76p-weqj).
If you have more questions about USTs, you can get in touch with the Site Assessment and Support Unit (SASU) at DEEP at this email: DEEP.Leakingust@ct.gov

I'm writing in response to your request for data on the CT Open Data Portal for data on property values, local businesses, and tax rates. I'll include links to a few datasets that I hope will help address your request below:

Real Estate Sales 2001-2021 GL - This dataset includes all real estate sales with a sales price of $2,000 or greater. It also includes the assessed value and sales amount for each property. It includes a street address and town for each property. (https://data.ct.gov/Housing-and-Development/Real-Estate-Sales-2001-2021-GL/5mzw-sjtu/about_data);
Tax Levy by Town, FY2019-2025 - This dataset includes the tax levy by town including the net levy for real property, personal property, motor vehicles, and supplemental motor vehicles. This data is reported at the town level. (https://data.ct.gov/Government/Tax-Levy-by-Town-FY-2019-2025/he33-brru/about_data);
Connecticut Business Registry - Business Master - This dataset includes all businesses registered with the Secretary of the State. It includes the street address, city, and zip for each business. (https://data.ct.gov/Business/Connecticut-Business-Registry-Business-Master/n7gp-d28j/about_data)

There are several datasets about UST on the Portal:
Regarding Tank Removal information, this data sets includes tank removal information in the column called Closure Type:
Underground Storage Tanks (USTs) - Facility and Tank Details (https://data.ct.gov/Environment-and-Natural-Resources/Underground-Storage-Tanks-USTs-Facility-and-Tank-D/utni-rddb); 
These 3 data sets may be of interest regarding Remediation:
Releases from Federally Regulated Underground Storage Tank Systems (https://data.ct.gov/Environment-and-Natural-Resources/Releases-from-Federally-Regulated-Underground-Stor/yc6z-jrb5);
List of Contaminated or Potentially Contaminated Sites - SASU Case Management System (https://data.ct.gov/Environment-and-Natural-Resources/List-of-Contaminated-or-Potentially-Contaminated-S/77ya-7twa);
